    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "From: Wim Coekaerts:\n\n> ... the binary and libraries and a bunch of ps1xml files are all in /usr/local/share/powershell. Would it make sense to separate them out in bin/ lib/ etc/ ? In fact, even though for ‘3rd party’ it’s typically a good idea to have things in /usr/local or so… at least in the old days, there’s also possibly /usr/ (like anything native) or /opt/Microsoft/ or so. This can be religious some times with some folks but I think a bit of a split of bin/lib would be good either way – location-wise usr/local/ is not bad but I am not sure if that’s typical any more.\n",
